[src:do-178c/do-178c] DO-178 requires documented bidirectional connections (called traces) between the certification artifacts.
[src:do-178c/do-178c] A traceability analysis is then used to ensure that each requirement is fulfilled by the source code, that each functional requirement is verified by test, that each line of source code has a purpose (is connected to a requirement), and so forth.
[src:do-178c/do-178c] Traceability analysis assesses the system's completeness.
[src:do-178c/do-178c] The rigor and detail of the certification artifacts is related to the software level.
[src:do-178c/do-178c] SC-205/WG-12 was responsible for revising DO-178B/ED-12B to bring it up to date with respect to current software development and verification technologies.
[src:do-178c/do-178c] The structure of the document remains largely the same from B to C.
